	('2021-06-0720:37:08', '\'Evil Dead Rise\' Director Shares Groovy Image To Mark First Day of Filming', '...', '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Director&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Lee Cronin</strong>&nbsp;has shared the first behind-the-scenes image from&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/tag/evil-dead-rise/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Evil Dead Rise</strong></em></a>&nbsp;to celebrate the start of production on the long-awaited fourth installment in the cult classic franchise, which was recently announced to be&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/evil-dead-4-where-to-watch/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">heading exclusively to HBO Max</a>.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Cronin also wrote the script, and though he’s relatively untested as a director, his feature debut&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">The Hole in the Ground</em></strong>&nbsp;was an accomplished and atmospheric supernatural chiller, while he comes with the seal of approval from&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Evil Dead</em>&nbsp;architects&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Sam Raimi</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Bruce Campbell</strong>, both of whom remain involved in&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Rise&nbsp;</em>as producers.</p><div class="body-img responsive-img img-article-item" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 421.875px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;"><figure style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0px; position: relative;"><picture style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="750px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/evil-dead-2.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><img class="img-responsive"  width="1920" height="1080" class=" lazyloaded" alt="evil-dead-2" style="box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 750px; height: auto; display: block;"></picture><figcaption class="body-img-caption" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5rem; position: absolute; z-index: 30; top: 0px; right: 0px; font-size: 1em; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-shadow: rgb(22, 22, 22) 0px 0px 3px;">Image via De Laurentis Entertainment Group</figcaption></figure></div><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span class="related-single" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(73, 191, 60); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 1rem 0px 1.5rem 3rem; border-left: 8px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); background-color: rgb(242, 252, 246);">RELATED:<a href="https://collider.com/why-the-evil-dead-musical-is-great/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 1rem;">Why The \'Evil Dead\' Musical Is One Of The Franchise\'s Best And Most Bizarre Installments</a></span></p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Evil Dead Rise</em>&nbsp;has been talked about for decades, but it wasn’t until after the 2013 remake had been released that Campbell and Raimi signaled their intentions to bring Ash back to the big screen. In mid-2019 Raimi reaffirmed his commitment to the project, but somewhere along the line, it morphed into a brand new story&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/evil-dead-4-bruce-campbell-filming-date-revealed/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">following two estranged sisters reconnecting in the city&nbsp;</a>before they get interrupted by an onslaught of Deadites, with&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Vikings</strong></em>’ Alyssa<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">&nbsp;Sutherland&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Jungle</strong></em>’s&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Lily Sullivan</strong>&nbsp;landing the two lead roles.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">When the HBO Max news broke, it was confirmed that Campbell isn’t set to reprise his role as Ash in any sort of meaningful capacity,&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/doctor-strange-2-bruce-campbell-fake-script-leak/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">but the man loves a cameo</a>, so it can’t completely be ruled out by any stretch of the imagination either.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Evil Dead</em>&nbsp;franchise has shown incredible staying power over the last 40 years, having spawned a semi-reboot of a sequel, a Medieval horror comedy to cap off the original trilogy, before&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Fede Alvarez</strong>’s gore-drenched remake was followed by TV spinoff&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Ash vs. Evil Dead</em></strong>, which ran for three seasons before getting canceled.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Things have been coming together in rapid succession for&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Evil Dead Rise</em>, with Sutherland and Sullivan only announced to be headlining the film less than two weeks ago, and now cameras are already rolling in New Zealand. There’s no release date announced as of yet, but realistically you’d imagine the streaming exclusive should be arriving in either the first or second quarter of 2022. You can see the first image below.</p><p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"></p></p><div class="w-rich w-twitter" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 3rem; padding: 0px; width: 750px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><div class="twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; display: flex; max-width: 550px; width: 550px;"><div class="twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; display: flex; max-width: 550px; width: 550px;"><iframe id="twitter-widget-0" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowtransparency="true" allowfullscreen="true" class="" title="Twitter Tweet" src="https://platform.twitter.com/embed/Tweet.html?dnt=false&amp;embedId=twitter-widget-0&amp;features=eyJ0ZndfZXhwZXJpbWVudHNfY29va2llX2V4cGlyYXRpb24iOnsiYnVja2V0IjoxMjA5NjAwLCJ2ZXJzaW9uIjpudWxsfSwidGZ3X2hvcml6b25fdHdlZXRfZW1iZWRfOTU1NSI6eyJidWNrZXQiOiJodGUiLCJ2ZXJzaW9uIjpudWxsfSwidGZ3X3R3ZWV0X2VtYmVkX2NsaWNrYWJpbGl0eV8xMjEwMiI6eyJidWNrZXQiOiJjb250cm9sIiwidmVyc2lvbiI6bnVsbH19&amp;frame=false&amp;hideCard=false&amp;hideThread=false&amp;id=1401655600233205763&amp;lang=en&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fcollider.com%2Fevil-dead-4-rise-set-photo-filming%2F&amp;sessionId=2dbf71a8d0677efc677945aa62b6278957ecaac0&amp;siteScreenName=collider&amp;theme=light&amp;widgetsVersion=82e1070%3A1619632193066&amp;width=550px" data-tweet-id="1401655600233205763" style="box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; position: static; visibility: visible; width: 550px; height: 577px; display: block; flex-grow: 1;"></iframe></div></div></div>', '2021-06-07 20:37:08', 'Movie News', 'http://sieucapvip1.ddns.net:8080/BlogAuto/DownloadImage?name_file=admin/2021-06-07 083637/ash-vs-evil-dead-bruce-campbell-04-social-featured.jpg'),
	('2021-06-0720:37:45', 'Paramount+ To Launch New Low-Cost Ad-Supported Plan With More Movies, Original Series, and Live Sports This Summer', '...', '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Paramount+ has announced a significant expansion to its content slate starting this summer, which will kick off with the exclusive premiere of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Mark Wahlberg</strong>\'s sci-fi action thriller&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/tag/infinite/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Infinite</em></strong></a>&nbsp;on the streaming service on June 10. According to a press release, the streamer also confirmed that more than 1,000 premium movies would be debuting in the available library starting that same day for subscribers, including award-winners, fan-favorites, and family-friendly titles, as well as a new sports package including hundreds of marquee soccer matches.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The new list of summer content will continue to release in the weeks following, including&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">PAW Patrol: The Movie</strong></em>, which will earn a tandem&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/paw-patrol-movie-trailer/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">theatrical and Paramount+ premiere</a>&nbsp;on August 20, as well as&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">A Quiet Place Part II</strong></em>, which will head to the streaming service&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/a-quiet-place-2-final-trailer/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">after its 45-day theatrical run</a>.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">“The breadth and depth of premium feature films and exclusive series coming to the service further strengthens our position in the market as a premium entertainment destination and, by offering this compelling content portfolio at an all-new low cost, makes us even more accessible to a wide consumer audience,” said&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Tom Ryan</strong>, President and Chief Executive Officer, ViacomCBS Streaming, in a statement provided to press.</p><div class="body-img responsive-img img-article-item" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 421.594px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;"><figure style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0px; position: relative;"><picture style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="750px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/p