b(22, 22, 22) 0px 0px 3px;">Image via Paramount+</figcaption></figure></div><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span class="related-single" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(73, 191, 60); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 1rem 0px 1.5rem 3rem; border-left: 8px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); background-color: rgb(242, 252, 246);">RELATED:<a href="https://collider.com/rugrats-revival-image-original-cast-paramount-plus/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 1rem;">\'Rugrats\' Is Coming Back With Its Original Cast And A Bold New Animation Style</a></span></p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Some of the films that will be available for Paramount+ customers to stream include&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Terminator: Dark Fate</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Skyfall</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">The Avengers</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Rocketman</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Judy</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Little Women</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Charlotte\'s Web</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Saint Maud</strong></em>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Crawl</strong></em>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Pet Sematary</em></strong>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Jackass Presents: Bad Grandpa</strong></em>, and&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">School of Rock</strong></em>. Original series programming includes the&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Rugrats</strong></em>&nbsp;reboot, the&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">iCarly</strong></em>&nbsp;revival series, which premieres on June 17, an all-new season of&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">The Good Fight</strong></em>&nbsp;premiering on June 24, and a new season of&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Star Trek: Lower Decks</strong></em>&nbsp;premiering on August 12.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">For soccer lovers, Paramount+\'s sports package will include the ability to stream hundreds of matches including Concacaf Men’s World Cup Qualifiers in June, the start of qualifiers for UEFA Champions League, UEFA Europa League, and UEFA Europa Conference League, the start of Italy’s Serie A season in August, and Argentina’s Liga Profesional de Fútbol, Campeonato Brasileirão Série A, and NWSL regular season competition throughout the summer.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The streamer has also confirmed they will be offering a new pricing tier for U.S. subscribers. The Essential Plan is an ad-supported tier at $4.99 per month, whereas the Premium Plan will also be available at $9.99 per month with commercial-free, on-demand entertainment with 4K, HDR, and Dolby Vision and mobile downloads. Each subscription option includes parental controls and up to six individual profiles. Later in June, a new watchlist feature called My List will also be rolled out on the service.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Paramount+ is now available to subscribers at a new low-cost tier of just $4.99 per month starting today. The service is available online at ParamountPlus.com; on mobile devices via the Paramount+ app for iOS and Android; and on Android TV, Amazon Prime Video Channels, Apple TV, Apple TV channels, Chromecast, Facebook Portal, Fire TV, LG Smart TVs, PlayStation 4, Roku Players, Samsung Smart TVs, Vizio Smartcast TVs and Xbox One. For more details, visit&nbsp;<a href="https://www.paramountplus.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">ParamountPlus.com</a>.</p>', '2021-06-07 20:37:45', 'Movie News', 'http://sieucapvip1.ddns.net:8080/BlogAuto/DownloadImage?name_file=admin/2021-06-07 083729/paramount-plus-movie-homepage-social-featured.jpg'),
	('2021-06-0720:43:51', '\'Loki\' Confirmed as Gender Fluid in Disney Plus Featurette, Will Lady Loki Show Up?', '...', '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">As<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">&nbsp;Loki</em></strong>’s premiere date draws closer, we’ve been getting some juicy featurettes and behind-the-scenes footage about the anticipated show. The latest promo video offered eagle-eyed viewers a specific detail that finally brings in a character and ability not seen in the MCU yet.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">We have already seen that Loki has the ability to disguise himself as other people. However, we have never seen him shapeshift into someone of the opposite sex. That appears to be changing, as the TVA’s folder lists Loki’s sex as fluid in a blink-and-you’ll-miss-it detail. This is just not an exciting addition of explicit LGBTQ+ representation in the MCU; this all but confirms the addition of Lady Loki in the show.</p><div class="body-img responsive-img img-article-item" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 375px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;"><figure style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0px; position: relative;"><picture style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="750px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><img class="img-responsive"  width="1700" height="850" class=" lazyloaded" alt="loki-tom-hiddleston-social-featured" style="box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 750px; height: auto; display: block;"></picture><figcaption class="body-img-caption" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5rem; position: absolute; z-index: 30; top: 0px; right: 0px; font-size: 1em; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-shadow: rgb(22, 22, 22) 0px 0px 3px;">Image via Disney+</figcaption></figure></div><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span class="related-single" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(73, 191, 60); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 1rem 0px 1.5rem 3rem; border-left: 8px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); background-color: rgb(242, 252, 246);">RELATED:<a href="https://collider.com/loki-show-reviews-reactions/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 1rem;">First \'Loki\' Social Reactions Say It\'s Funny, Weird, And Takes The MCU In A New Direction</a></span></p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">To get you caught up, Lady Loki is essentially no different from the Loki we’ve come to know and love. Although, she does have one major difference, and that is that she was created after the god inhabited a human body previously meant for the spirit of Lady Sif. Loki was able to take over this body, using it in recent years to do what he does best: trick and manipulate. In the 2019 novel&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Loki: Where Mischief Lies&nbsp;</em></strong>by author&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Mackenzi Lee</strong>, Loki’s gender fluidity and pansexuality were confirmed as canon, at least in the current comic timeline. It looks like it might become canon in the MCU as well.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">No matter how Loki’s gender fluidity is introduced into the show, it is an element of his character that is quite welcome. Given how integral Lady Loki has become to Loki’s character in newer comic arcs, her possible appearance is exciting.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Loki&nbsp;</em>premieres on Disney+ on Wednesday, June 9th. The show has been getting great reviews so far, so get hyped with the featurettes below.</p>', '2021-06-07 20:43:51', 'Movie News', 'http://sieucapvip1.ddns.net:8080/BlogAuto/DownloadImage?name_file=admin/2021-06-07 084337/New-Loki-Clip.jpg'),
	('2021-06-0720:44:28', '\'The Conjuring 3\' Scares \'A Quiet Place 2\' Away at Weekend Box Office', '...', '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">As expected,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;"><a href="https://collider.com/tag/the-conjuring-3/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s;">The Conjuring: The Devil Made Me Do It</a></em></strong>&nbsp;won the weekend at the box office, and while the estimated $24 million is slightly lower than the $25 million being predicted, it’s another big win for the theatrical industry in general, whichever way you want to look at it.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The third installment in the series, and eighth entry overall in&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">The Conjuring</em>&nbsp;Universe, scored the third-biggest debut of the pandemic era behind&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">A Quiet Place Part II&nbsp;</strong></em>and&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Godzilla vs. Kong</strong></em>, and the fifth number one movie for studio Warner Bros. this year, despite all of them getting simultaneous HBO Max releases.</p><div class="body-img responsive-img img-article-item" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 375px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;"><figure style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0px; position: relative;"><picture style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="750px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/the-conjuring-3.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><img class="img-responsive"  width="1200" height="600" class=" lazyloaded" alt="the-conjuring-3" style="box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 750px; height: auto; display: block;"></picture><figcaption class="body-img-caption" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5rem; position: absolute; z-index: 30; top: 0px; right: 0px; font-size: 1em; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-shadow: rgb(22, 22, 22) 0px 0px 3px;">Image via Warner Bros.</figcaption></figure></div><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span class="related-single" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(73, 191, 60); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 1rem 0px 1.5rem 3rem; border-left: 8px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); background-color: rgb(242, 252, 246);">RELATED:<a href="https://collider.com/the-conjuring-3-director-interview-michael-chaves/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 1rem;">\'The Conjuring 3\' Director Michael Chaves On Approaching The Franchise As A Fan First</a></span></p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Last week’s&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/a-quiet-place-2-friday-box-office/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">record-breaking champion</a>&nbsp;took a sizeable hit after dropping almost 60% in its second frame to $19.5 million, which also deprived us of being able to say for the first time in close to a year and a half that two titles earned at least $20 million apiece in consecutive weekends, after&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">John Krasinski</strong>’s horror sequel and Disney’s&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Cruella&nbsp;</em></strong>both managed the feat during the last three-day weekend. So close, cinemas, so close.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">However, in more good news, should&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">A Quiet Place Part II</em>&nbsp;earn another $12 million throughout the rest of its run, then it’ll become the first film since&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Sonic the Hedgehog</em></strong>&nbsp;arrived in February 2020 to bring in over $100 million from domestic screens, with the video game adaptation the one and only effort released last year to hit that milestone. That being said,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Godzilla vs. Kong</em>&nbsp;is $881,332 away from the milestone, so it remains to be seen which blockbuster reaches it first.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Speaking of the Mouse House’s origin story,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Cruella&nbsp;</em>took third with just over $11.2 million&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/cruella-sequel-movie-in-development/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">as sequel talks continue</a>&nbsp;behind the scenes, the animated&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Spirit Untamed</strong></em>&nbsp;opened in fourth with an underwhelming $6.2 million, with the rest of the Top 10 filled out by longtime holdovers&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Wrath of Man, Raya and the Last Dragon, Spiral</strong>,&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Godzilla vs. Kong</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;">Demon Slayer: Mugen Train</em></strong>, with drama&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Dream Horse&nbsp;</strong></em>bringing up the rear in its third weekend. It’s been another win for the horror genre, but blockbuster season is almost upon us, so hopefully the box office will continue to rebound.</p>', '2021-06-07 20:44:28', 'Movie News', 'http://sieucapvip1.ddns.net:8080/BlogAuto/DownloadImage?name_file=admin/2021-06-07 084416/the-conjuring-3-social-featured.jpg'),
	('2021-06-0720:45:22', 'Classic \'GoldenEye 007\' N64 Game Has Been Recreated in \'Far Cry 5\' Giving Us HD Remake We\'ve Always Wanted', '...', '<p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Fans of the N64 probably remember hours spent sitting in front of the television playing through&nbsp;<a href="https://collider.com/tag/goldeneye-007/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;"><em style="box-sizing: inherit;"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">GoldenEye 007</strong></em></a>&nbsp;(and fighting about who got to cheat and play as Oddjob). The 1997 game has now been brought back to life! Well, sort of. A YouTuber has created a version of&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">GoldenEye 007</em>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit;">Far Cry 5</strong></em>’s level editor. Finally, our dream of playing this game and going back to the Silo map, this time without the clunky aiming system, can live on.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><strong style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Krollywood</strong>, the YouTuber who spent 1,400 hours recreating the iconic game, spoke with&nbsp;<a href="https://kotaku.com/heres-goldeneye-007-remade-from-the-ground-up-in-far-cr-1847040225" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">Kotaku</a>&nbsp;about it. In a direct message, revealed that the recreation includes every level of the 90s game with the exception of the two bonus levels.&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Far Cry 5</em>&nbsp;isn’t the only game with the ability to edit levels but, for Krollywood, it is better because of its number of objects at your disposal. And it clearly worked out in all our favor because this version of&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">GoldenEye 007</em>&nbsp;is hitting us right in the nostalgia.</p><div class="body-img responsive-img img-article-item" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 500px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;"><figure style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 0px; position: relative;"><picture style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" sizes="750px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=750&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 768px)" sizes="943px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=943&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 481px)" sizes="767px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=767&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><source media="(min-width: 0px)" sizes="480px" data-srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" srcset="https://static1.colliderimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/goldeneye-007-n64.jpg?q=50&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=480&amp;dpr=1.5" style="box-sizing: inherit;"><img class="img-responsive"  width="1200" height="800" class=" lazyloaded" alt="goldeneye-007-n64" style="box-sizing: inherit; border: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 750px; height: auto; display: block;"></picture><figcaption class="body-img-caption" style="box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5rem; position: absolute; z-index: 30; top: 0px; right: 0px; font-size: 1em; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-shadow: rgb(22, 22, 22) 0px 0px 3px;">Image via Nintendo</figcaption></figure></div><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span class="related-single" style="box-sizing: inherit; display: block; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(73, 191, 60); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 1rem 0px 1.5rem 3rem; border-left: 8px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); background-color: rgb(242, 252, 246);">RELATED:<a href="https://collider.com/goldeneye-007-oddjob-cheating/" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize; line-height: 1.4; margin-top: 1rem;">‘Goldeneye 007’ Creator Confirms Once And For All: Playing As Oddjob Is Cheating</a></span></p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The first-person shooter game was one that captivated a generation for its revolutionary multiplayer deathmatch mode that set the standard for multiplayer games going forward. That the game also included inventive gameplay that required more stealth than earlier FPS games, certainly made an impression.&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">GoldenEye</em>&nbsp;was wildly popular, consuming the Nintendo 64 fans of the 90s, and it’s still considered one of the best games of all time, and certainly among the best movie-to-game adaptations ever.</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">In a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/PS4/comments/nrygek/im_a_big_fan_of_editors_and_goldeneye_007_so_i/h0jmhro?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=web2x&amp;context=3" style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32); outline: none; padding: 0px 2px; border-radius: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(73, 191, 60); border-left: none; border-image: initial; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s; font-weight: 700;">Reddit&nbsp;</a>comment, Krollywood said that the levels are available to play via arcade mode with&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(26, 65, 32);">Far Cry 5</em>. You can look up the PSN username “Perfect-Dark1982.”</p><p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 3rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.125em; color: rgb(22, 22, 22); line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">As a proper HD remaster of&nbsp;<em style